  {
    "_id": "project_smart_library_management_system",
    "slug": "smart-library-management-system",
    "title": "Smart Library Management System",

    "description": {
      "short": "A Java desktop library management system with MVC architecture and MS Access integration.",
      "full": "Smart Library Management System is a Java-based desktop application designed to manage core library operations through a structured MVC-style architecture. The system separates concerns into UI, controllers, and models, enabling maintainability and clarity in business logic handling. It integrates with a bundled Microsoft Access database using UCanAccess (JDBC), allowing persistent storage without requiring a separate database server. The application supports essential workflows including authentication, book and inventory management, member handling, issue/return processes, fine tracking, and audit logging. It is built using a simple classpath-based execution model with direct javac/java commands and bundled dependencies, making it lightweight and easy to run without modern build tools."
    },

